olive oil
2 potato
1 parsnip
2 tbs milk
40 g butter
¼ tsp salt
1 carrot
1 bag baby spinach leaves
2 clove garlic
1 packet beef strips
½ sachet Seasoning Blend
½ packet cream
1 bag parsley

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with
boiling water.
• Peel potato and parsnip, then cut both into
large chunks.
• Cook potato and parsnip in the boiling water,
over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork,
10-15 minutes.
• Drain and return to saucepan.
• Add the milk, butter and the salt to the veggies.
Mash until smooth and cover to keep warm.

Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help
mash the veggies!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice carrot into sticks.
Finely chop garlic.
• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook carrot, tossing,
until just tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add half the garlic and cook until fragrant,
2-3 minutes. Stir through baby spinach leaves
until wilted, 1 minute.
• Season with salt and pepper, then transfer to a
bowl. Cover to keep warm.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches,
tossing, until browned and cooked through,
1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat
helps it stay tender.

• Return the frying pan to medium heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. Cook seasoning blend (see
ingredients) and remaining garlic until fragrant,
1 minute.
• Reduce the heat to low, then add a dash of
water and scrape up any bits stuck to the
bottom of the pan.
• Add cream (see ingredients) and cook, stirring,
until slightly thickened, 1-2 minutes.
• Return beef and any resting juices to the pan,
then stir to combine.

• Divide veggie mash, creamy beef and garlic
veggies between bowls.
• Tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!